quickjs.library/QJS_ResolveModule               quickjs.library/QJS_ResolveModule

    NAME
	QJS_ResolveModule -- Force module resolution for a
	    compiled module value.

    SYNOPSIS
	rc = QJS_ResolveModule(ctx, obj_ptr)
	D0                     A0   A1

	LONG QJS_ResolveModule(JSContext *ctx,
			       const JSValue *obj_ptr);

    FUNCTION
	Runs the module resolution phase on a value returned by
	QJS_Eval() with JS_EVAL_FLAG_COMPILE_ONLY (i.e. a
	compiled-but-not-yet-linked module).  Needed only for
	pre-compiled bytecode workflows; normal use doesn't
	require this.

    INPUTS
	ctx	- Host context.
	obj_ptr - Pointer to the compiled module value.

    RESULT
	rc - 0 on success, non-zero on failure.

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_Eval, QJS_EvalFunction


quickjs.library/QJS_GetScriptOrModuleName   QJS_GetScriptOrModuleName

    NAME
	QJS_GetScriptOrModuleName -- Walk the call stack and
	    return the filename of an enclosing script/module.

    SYNOPSIS
	atom = QJS_GetScriptOrModuleName(ctx, n_stack_levels)
	D0                               A0   D0

	JSAtom QJS_GetScriptOrModuleName(JSContext *ctx,
					 int n_stack_levels);

    FUNCTION
	Returns the filename atom of the N'th enclosing call
	frame's script/module (0 = current, 1 = caller, etc.).
	Useful for implementing `import.meta.url`-style
	reflection in native code.

	Release with QJS_FreeAtom().

    INPUTS
	ctx	       - Host context.
	n_stack_levels - Depth to walk (0-based).

    RESULT
	atom - Filename atom, or JS_ATOM_NULL if the requested
	       level is outside the current call chain.

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_GetImportMeta, QJS_AtomToCStringLen


quickjs.library/QJS_Malloc                           quickjs.library/QJS_Malloc

    NAME
	QJS_Malloc -- Allocate memory tracked by the engine.

    SYNOPSIS
	ptr = QJS_Malloc(ctx, size)
	D0                A0   D0

	APTR QJS_Malloc(JSContext *ctx, ULONG size);

    FUNCTION
	Allocates `size` bytes from the engine's pool.  The
	allocation counts toward the runtime's memory limit, so
	it can fail if QJS_SetMemoryLimit() would be exceeded.

	Use this (rather than AmigaOS AllocMem) for buffers that
	are conceptually engine-owned, so the memory limit and
	OOM behaviour stay accurate.

    INPUTS
	ctx  - Host context.
	size - Bytes to allocate.

    RESULT
	ptr - Pointer to the buffer, or NULL on OOM.  Free with
	      QJS_Free().

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_Free, QJS_Realloc, QJS_Calloc, QJS_Mallocz


quickjs.library/QJS_Mallocz                         quickjs.library/QJS_Mallocz

    NAME
	QJS_Mallocz -- Allocate zero-initialized memory.

    SYNOPSIS
	ptr = QJS_Mallocz(ctx, size)
	D0                 A0   D0

	APTR QJS_Mallocz(JSContext *ctx, ULONG size);

    FUNCTION
	Like QJS_Malloc() but the buffer is zero-filled before
	being returned.

    INPUTS
	ctx  - Host context.
	size - Bytes to allocate.

    RESULT
	ptr - Pointer to the buffer, or NULL on OOM.

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_Malloc, QJS_Calloc


quickjs.library/QJS_Calloc                           quickjs.library/QJS_Calloc

    NAME
	QJS_Calloc -- Allocate an array of zero-initialized items.

    SYNOPSIS
	ptr = QJS_Calloc(ctx, count, size)
	D0                A0   D0     D1

	APTR QJS_Calloc(JSContext *ctx, ULONG count, ULONG size);

    FUNCTION
	Allocates `count * size` bytes, zero-filled.  Equivalent
	to QJS_Mallocz(count * size) but performs the
	multiplication safely (returns NULL on overflow).

    INPUTS
	ctx   - Host context.
	count - Number of items.
	size  - Size of each item.

    RESULT
	ptr - Pointer to the buffer, or NULL.

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_Malloc, QJS_Mallocz


quickjs.library/QJS_Realloc                         quickjs.library/QJS_Realloc

    NAME
	QJS_Realloc -- Resize an engine-tracked allocation.

    SYNOPSIS
	ptr2 = QJS_Realloc(ctx, ptr, size)
	D0                 A0   A1   D0

	APTR QJS_Realloc(JSContext *ctx, APTR ptr, ULONG size);

    FUNCTION
	Resizes `ptr` to `size` bytes.  May move the allocation;
	always use the returned pointer thereafter and discard
	the old one.

	Passing NULL `ptr` is equivalent to QJS_Malloc().
	Passing 0 `size` is equivalent to QJS_Free() and returns
	NULL.

    INPUTS
	ctx  - Host context.
	ptr  - Existing pointer or NULL.
	size - New size in bytes, or 0.

    RESULT
	ptr2 - Pointer to the (possibly moved) buffer, or NULL on
	       OOM (in which case the original ptr is unchanged).

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_Malloc, QJS_Free


quickjs.library/QJS_Free                                 quickjs.library/QJS_Free

    NAME
	QJS_Free -- Release memory allocated with QJS_Malloc() or
	    friends.

    SYNOPSIS
	QJS_Free(ctx, ptr)
		 A0   A1

	VOID QJS_Free(JSContext *ctx, APTR ptr);

    FUNCTION
	Frees a buffer previously returned by QJS_Malloc(),
	QJS_Mallocz(), QJS_Calloc(), QJS_Realloc(),
	QJS_Strdup(), or QJS_WriteObject().  NULL is accepted
	and ignored.

    INPUTS
	ctx - Host context.
	ptr - Pointer to free, or NULL.

    RESULT
	None.

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_Malloc, QJS_Strdup, QJS_WriteObject


quickjs.library/QJS_Strdup                           quickjs.library/QJS_Strdup

    NAME
	QJS_Strdup -- Duplicate a C string into engine memory.

    SYNOPSIS
	str2 = QJS_Strdup(ctx, str)
	D0                A0   A1

	STRPTR QJS_Strdup(JSContext *ctx, CONST_STRPTR str);

    FUNCTION
	Allocates a copy of the NUL-terminated string `str` via
	QJS_Malloc().  Useful for stashing user-supplied strings
	in long-lived structures.

    INPUTS
	ctx - Host context.
	str - Source string.

    RESULT
	str2 - Newly-allocated copy, or NULL on OOM.  Release
	       with QJS_Free().

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_Malloc, QJS_Free


quickjs.library/QJS_AddBaseObjects             quickjs.library/QJS_AddBaseObjects

    NAME
	QJS_AddBaseObjects -- Install Object, Array, Function,
	    Error, Math, etc.

    SYNOPSIS
	rc = QJS_AddBaseObjects(ctx)
	D0                      A0

	LONG QJS_AddBaseObjects(JSContext *ctx);

    FUNCTION
	Installs the foundational ECMAScript intrinsics on the
	context: Object, Array, Function, Error,
	{TypeError, RangeError, ...}, Math, JSON (the namespace
	object), Number, String, Boolean, Symbol primitives,
	plus their prototypes.

	Required if you started with QJS_NewContextRaw(); already
	called for you by QJS_NewContext().

    INPUTS
	ctx - Target context.

    RESULT
	rc - 0 on success, non-zero on failure.

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_NewContextRaw, QJS_AddJSON, QJS_AddDate


quickjs.library/QJS_AddEval                         quickjs.library/QJS_AddEval

    NAME
	QJS_AddEval -- Install the eval() global function.

    SYNOPSIS
	QJS_AddEval(ctx)
		    A0

	VOID QJS_AddEval(JSContext *ctx);

    FUNCTION
	Adds the global `eval()` function.  Required if you
	want JS code to run dynamically-constructed source.

    INPUTS
	ctx - Target context.

    RESULT
	None.

    SEE ALSO
	QJS_NewContextRaw, QJS_AddBaseObjects


quickjs.library/QJS_AddDate                         quickjs.library/QJS_AddDate

    NAME
	QJS_AddDate -- Install the Date constructor.

    SYNOPSIS
	QJS_AddDate(ctx)
		    A0

	VOID QJS_AddDate(JSContext *ctx);

    FUNCTION
	Adds the Date constructor and its prototype.  Date.now(),
	Date.parse(), instance methods like .toISOString() all
	become available.

